text:
Let's just say it 3 Guys you have nothing on Cugino's. OMG my son has told me about this place and I have been dying to go here for some time. It is a very popular place for many of the UNLV students and there is good reason. The storefront is like walking into little Italy, it is a very happy and an open atmosphere. Right from the start it smells like those old fashion deli's that use to be here in SF. I knew right there I was in heaven. The counter has many delicious salads and of course desserts like this delicious silky cheese cake which I ordered. They also have many delicious cookies and Italian food which gets shipped from New Jersey. The family who runs this business are very sweet and welcoming. They welcome you with a warm smile and it's like being on the East Coast when you hear their accent it is absolutely charming. 
Now let's talk about the food, I finally had like a real calzone and I mean it was so delicious and bigggggggggggg. The sauce was so amazing and it was fresh so you don't get heartburn like you would from business that use canned products, this sauce was made fresh and from scratch.  I barely could finish it and Timmy had this Italian sub and my brother also had the same thing as him. The sandwich was a true Italian sub and again since it is all made fresh you don't experience any heartburn. 

We also bought these delicious Italian cookies. So I encourage all who go to Vegas stop by this shop, the prices are cheap compared to what you would pay in the Bay or on the strip and again you have real Italians from the East making this food and a REAL CALZONE! Next time I am going to go for their famous pizza which they are known for all over Vegas as having the best pizza. I am not going to lie though I am going to have that cheese cake because I haven't had one that tasted that good since the Elk's club and again that was made by Masonaries :} from the EAST COAST. :}
